                            <comment id="12867540" author="stuhood" created="Fri, 14 May 2010 15:56:00 +0000"  >&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The synchronized methods don&apos;t seem necessary: all structures are concurrent, and I don&apos;t think we need any operations to compose&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;getPendingFiles has a race between &apos;streamManagers.containsKey(host)&apos; and &apos;get(host)&apos;: perhaps just perform a single get, and check for null&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Other than that, looks good to me.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
